-- GM, Ford sink after S&P says it may cut debt ratings
-- 
-- Fri Jun 20, 2008 2:11pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/20/us-markets-stocks-autos-idUSN2046993520080620

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of General Motors Corp ( GM.N ) and Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) plummeted after credit ratings agency Standard & Poor's said it may cut the U.S. automakers' ratings.  

 GM shares fell 5.9 percent to $13.92 on the New York Stock Exchange, while shares of Ford declined 7.4 percent to $5.85. (Reporting by  Ellis Mnyandu ; Editing by  Jan Paschal )